# E2E Browser (`e2e/browser/`)

## Definition

- Full UI flow through the browser to the backend (Playwright).
- Specs: `e2e/browser/*.spec.js`; shared helpers: `e2e/browser/testHelpers.js`, `globalSetup.js`, `globalHooks.js`.

## Running

- Playwright uses **4 workers** (parallel spec files; tests within a file stay ordered).
- From repo root: `npm run e2e` (runs port release / DB reset per project script when configured).
- If ports 8080 / 5173 are in use or running manually: `powershell -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File scripts/release-e2e-ports.ps1` first (see `workflow.mdc`).

## Combat pacing vs production

- **Production** UI delays (per log line, map/encounter/rest gaps, etc.) live in [`frontend/src/game/combatPacing.js`](../../frontend/src/game/combatPacing.js): `DEFAULT_COMBAT_LOG_STEP_DELAY_MS`, `COMBAT_PACING_MS`, `getCombatLogStepDelayMs()`.
- **E2E fast mode** is explicit: `e2eFastCombat` in `localStorage` and/or `?e2e=1` on the URL; [`globalHooks.js`](../../e2e/browser/globalHooks.js) injects the flag before each document load. `applyCombatPacingDelayMs()` then uses **0ms** so tests do not inherit production wait times.
- Do not rely on generic browser automation signals for pacing; keep test vs live separation in `combatPacing.js` + E2E hooks.

## Implementation

- ASCII only in spec and helper source.
- Follow patterns in existing specs; for new coverage, see [.cursor/skills/text-idle-add-e2e-test/SKILL.md](.cursor/skills/text-idle-add-e2e-test/SKILL.md).
- After closing one skill milestone modal, other heroes may still have queued modals (shared combat XP): use `dismissQueuedSkillChoiceModals` from `testHelpers.js` (after `pauseCombat` when needed) before clicking main-screen UI behind overlays.
- To switch the hero detail modal to the Skills tab when a `SkillChoiceModal` overlay would block Playwright pointer hits, use `clickHeroDetailSkillsTab` from `testHelpers.js` (DOM `click()` on the second tab button).

## Doc sync

- New or changed user flows: update specs **and** the artifacts listed in **Doc and Test Sync** (`workflow.mdc`) in the **same change**. E2E must not be the only updated surface while design docs or requirements examples stay stale.
